      "message": "I find the pagination discussion confusing, because paging is transparent to the application and is not something we normally have to think about.\n\nThe fundamental issue appears to be a buffer underflow, where we attempt to read before the beginning of a client-provided buffer.\n\n(whether or not we crash does depend on memory layout and which addresses are mapped;  but the trigger/root cause is an OOB read)",
